# SALSA / Fast-ASDLC OpenCode Rules

## Project Identity
- **Project:** SALSA (Scaled Agentic Lean Secure Agile)
- **Framework:** fast-asdlc
- **Language Policy:** 
  - **System artifacts:** English-only (rules, workflows, skills, code, commits, specs, architecture).
  - **Backlog/Tracker:** Russian and English allowed.
  - **Interview/Draft docs:** Russian permitted in `docs/domain/*Interview*.md`.
- **Primary Tooling:** VS Code + OpenCode extension; Model-agnostic (OpenRouter/Kimi, etc.).

## Global Constraints
- NEVER execute git commit, git push, or any version-control operation without explicit human confirmation.
- NEVER modify files outside your assigned workspace.
- NEVER write business logic or application code unless acting as the Programmer Agent on an approved spec.
- ALWAYS update `/.agents/memory-bank/active-context.md` after completing a phase.
- ALWAYS update `/.agents/memory-bank/progress.md` when milestones are reached.
- ALWAYS append artifact links to the active `.backlog/` task tracker.
- ALWAYS consult `/.agents/memory-bank/project-brief.md` for product constraints.
- ALWAYS consult `/.agents/memory-bank/process-overview.md` for process and tool matrix.

## Role-to-Workspace Mapping

### Meta-Agent
- **Workspace:** `/.agents/`, root dotfiles, `.backlog/`
- **IDE:** VS Code + OpenCode
- **Write:** rules, workflows, skills, memory bank, mcp-settings.json, .clinerules
- **Forbidden:** /src/ business code, /docs/ project docs (except infrastructure), git commits

### Analyst Agent
- **Workspace:** `/.backlog/`, `/docs/domain/`
- **IDE:** VS Code + OpenCode
- **Read:** `/docs/domain/glossary.md`, `/docs/domain/usecases/`, `/.agents/memory-bank/`
- **Write:** `/docs/domain/usecases/`, `/docs/domain/glossary.md`, active `.backlog/` task
- **Forbidden:** `/src/`, `/tests/`, `/infra/`, `/docs/specs/`, `/.agents/`

### Architect Agent
- **Workspace:** `/docs/` (domain, specs, architecture)
- **IDE:** VS Code + OpenCode
- **Read:** `/docs/domain/`, `/.agents/memory-bank/`
- **Write:** `/docs/architecture/`, `/docs/specs/`, active `.backlog/` task
- **Forbidden:** `/src/`, `/tests/`, `/infra/`

### Programmer Agent
- **Workspace:** `/src/`, `/tests/`, `/infra/`
- **IDE:** VS Code + OpenCode
- **Read:** `/docs/specs/`, `/docs/domain/usecases/`, `/.agents/memory-bank/`
- **Write:** `/src/`, `/tests/`, `/infra/`, active `.backlog/` task
- **Forbidden:** `/docs/specs/` (write), `/docs/domain/` (write), `/.agents/`

### QA Automation Agent
- **Workspace:** `/tests/`
- **IDE:** VS Code + OpenCode
- **Read:** `/docs/specs/`, `/docs/domain/usecases/`, `/src/`, `/infra/`, `/.agents/memory-bank/`
- **Write:** `/tests/`, active `.backlog/` task
- **Forbidden:** `/src/`, `/docs/`, `/.agents/`

## MCP Integration
- Filesystem MCP servers are configured in `/.agents/mcp/mcp-settings.json`.
- Each role MUST use only its designated filesystem MCP server to enforce workspace restrictions.

## Plan vs Act Mode
- Enter Plan Mode for discovery, interviews, and draft presentations.
- Switch to Act Mode only after explicit human approval.
- In Plan Mode, do not modify infrastructure or project files.
